  "course_description": "Selected contemporary problems in memory, language, learning, and thinking. May be repeated when the topic changes.",
  "course_notes": "Topic Title: \"Humans of Tomorrow: Integrating Technology with Humanity.\" Prior completion of PSYC 110 and PSYC 111 and QTM 100 and a course in [PSYC 200 plus level or NBB 200 plus level]. Permission of the instructor is required for enrollment. For permission, e-mail Dr. Kelly at aubrey.kelly@emory.edu with relevant courses you have taken in PSYC, NBB, PHIL, and Computer Science. This course will focus on the biological, cultural, and technological evolution of life on Earth. We will examine the impact of our modern technological world on the human brain, body, and behavior, and consider the future trajectory of our species. Discussions will explore topics such as gene-editing, intelligence, consciousness, and consider a future with artificial general intelligence and technologically enhanced humans. Because discussions on futurism will revolve around both the inevitable and the plausible, we will also consider ethical issues related to current and future technologies and broadly discuss goals for humanity.",
